<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A1586-2003Jan16.html">www.washingtonpost.com/wp...Jan16.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
And for all those folks who think the US screws up countries with our foreign policies, American screw-ups can't hold a candle to Iraqi and North Korean screw-ups.  Those two countries are starving their entire populations, locking up three generations of families in Nazi-style internment camps if one family member makes an unapproved statement, repeatedly raping/torturing/murdering anyone they like.  We could go in and cause a total disaster and it'd still be better than it was before we came in.  And truly demonic behavior by the enemy is conveniently ignored.<br>
<br>
Try Afghanistan for example, if we hadn't invaded, millions of Afghanis would have starved to death last winter, instead we overthrew the oppressive regime and saved millions of lives.  But the anti-war crowd ignores all that and focuses the media on the wedding celebration where the people were firing machine guns in the air while US aircraft were overhead, resulting in the accidental killing of a few dozen people.  Anything less that perfect sainthood from the USA and allies constitutes demonic behavior, by their logic. <p>Zolina the Wind Caller, Forest Stalker of Healers United, Quellious<br>
