<br>
You're a step father/mother taking care of your daughter-in-law.  She smokes some weed on the weekends and you know it to be true.  You have no real evidence of it except you smell a hint of it on her.  She *might* just be around people who are smoking it and not smoking it, but you find her guilty by association. (i.e. she shouldnt be around those people anyway)  So, she wants to go to a party this friday night, but instead of letting her go, (cause you are sure she'll smoke some pot!) you tell her she can't go.  In fact, you have a whole new set of rules for her to live by!!  And instead of taking her word for it, you're going to inspect her room as much as you can so you can find ways of grounding her.  In your eyes a cigarette or a condom also justifies grounding.  She keeps living in the same world but you're inspecting and accusing her of smoking pot all the time.<br>
<br>
OK!<br>
<br>
How do you expect her to react?  The truth is, she might have been smoking pot, but instead of taking the actions you took you might have had better luck by helping her see what she's doing is wrong.  Maybe even convince her friends to help her fix her problems, but the WORST thing you could possibly do (except for nothing) is to take the offensive.  <br>
<br>
My point is, be creative with solutions.  War might be the easiest thing to do other than nothing, but IMO it's the wrong choice.  I like the idea of Saudi's pushing for a coup. <p>**********Quellious*********<br>
